Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_glitch_thresholds(25.10)                report_glitch_thresholds(25.10)

Name
       report_glitch_thresholds  -  Reports user-defined glitch thresholds ap-
       plied on library or instance pins

Syntax
       report_glitch_thresholds

        [-help]

       [-failure_point {input | output}]

        [-glitch_type <<string>>]

       [-instance_pins <<string>>]

        [-library_pins <<string>>]

       [-list_unannotated_instance_pins]

        [-list_unannotated_library_pins]

       [-view <string>]

       Reports user-defined glitch thresholds applied on library  or  instance
       pins.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -failure_point {input | output}
              Specifies if threshold failure point is input or output.

              Default: input

       -glitch_type <<string>>
              You  can  specify one or more glitch types (space-separated) for
              reporting. The valid options are: vl,  vh, vlu, vho, and all.

              When the -glitch_type parameter is  specified,  only  the  user-
              specified glitch types will be checked.

              Default: all

       -instance_pins <<string>>
              Specifies a list of instance pin names.

       -library_pins <<string>>
              Specifies a list of library pin names to be reported.

       -list_unannotated_instance_pins
              Reports list un-annotated instance pins.

              Reports  all  the  instance  input pins which do not have glitch
              threshold applied.

       -list_unannotated_library_pins
              Shows a list of all the library input pins which are not covered
              by library  pin-based/corresponding  library  cell-based  glitch
              threshold.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the view name.

Examples
              * The   following  report  shows  instance-pin  specific  glitch
                threshold summary:

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                               Instance-Pin Glitch Thresholds Summary

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                | Glitch Type | Inst Pin Count   | Annotated (%) |  Not  Anno-
                tated (%)|

                +-----------------+--------------+--------------------+-------------+

                |  VL           |  153001            |  21075 13.77%  | 131926
                86.23 %   |

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                | VH          | 153001            |  21075  13.77%   |  131926
                86.23 %   |

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                |  VLU          |  153001            |  0 0.00 %      | 153001
                100.00%   |

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                | VHO         | 153001           |   0  0.00  %      |  153001
                100.00%   |

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------+

                The  following  section  of  the  above  report shows library-
                cell/library-pin specific glitch threshold summary:

                              Library-Pin Glitch Thresholds Summary

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------------+

                | Glitch Type | Lib Pin Count   | Annotated (%)    | Not Anno-
                tated (%)|

                +-----------------+--------------+--------------------+-------------------+

                VL             |      742          |0   0.00%             |742
                100.00%

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------------+

                VH             |      742          |0  0.00%            |  742
                100.00%

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------------+

                VLU           |     742         |653 88.01%        |89 ll.99%

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------------+

                VHO           |     742         |653 88.01%        |89 11.99%

                +-------------------------------------------------------------------------+

